For this task, I used Canva to create a digital literacy awareness infographic.
Canva is a free online design platform that provides many templates, icons, and visual elements that help in creating professional-looking infographics easily.
Using this platform, I designed a single visual slide explaining the concept of digital literacy, useful digital tools for students, safe internet practices,
and email etiquette. The infographic was created to help students understand how digital skills are important in academic and professional life.
While creating the infographic, I practised organizing information visually instead of writing long paragraphs. I learned how to present key ideas using icons,
short text, and simple design elements so that the information becomes easy to understand. One interesting part of the task was choosing the right visuals and 
layout to make the infographic clear and attractive.
These tools will help me academically because they improve my ability to communicate information visually, create presentations, 
and share knowledge effectively. Digital design platforms like Canva are useful for making assignments, reports, and presentations more engaging and professional.
